http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/A-cross-cultural-experience-for-NCC-cadets/article14003121.ece

It was a memorable experience for the NCC cadets who have come from different parts of the country for the National Integration Camp (NIC) held on the premises of Bapatla Arts and Science College campus in the coastal town.More than 600 cadets from across the country, from the far corners of North Eastern States to the southern tip of Tamil Nadu, participated in the 12-day camp organised by the NCC Directorate of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.“The activities in the NIC camp are designed with the theme ‘Unity in Diversity’,” Group Commander, Guntur GP Headquarters, NCC, Col. B. Harikrishna Naidu told The Hindu on Saturday.Over 600 cadets from across the country participate in the 12-day camp organised by the NCC Directorate of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.